definition[0]: if a container or place fills up, or if you fill it up, it becomes full
example[0]: Her eyes filled up with tears.
example[1]: Shall I fill the car up  (=with petrol)?
definition[1]: to eat so much food that you cannot eat any more
example[2]: Don’t fill yourself up with cookies.
example[3]: He filled up on pecan pie.
definition[2]: food that fills you up makes you feel as though you have eaten a lot when you have only eaten a small amount
definition[3]: to gradually become full of people, things, or a substance
example[4]: Shares on the Stock Market began to rise, and industry reported order books filling up.
example[5]: The Antrim Technology Park is filling up with high technology software companies.
